# 1. レッツ体作り！

Emu: Hi, everyone! Good mornin-nin-ninja☆
Nene: Morning, Emu. I guess you came up with another weird greeting today...
Emu: Hehe♪ I'm trying to think like a ninja since we've been practicing to do a historical drama!
Rui: Hehe. Some may object to the idea of a ninja greeting others by saying, “Good morning.”
Rui: But I can tell that you're very excited about getting to be a part of “Ginnosuke's on the Case!”
Rui: In truth, I'm also looking forward to it. A number of aspects will be different from our usual performances, such as getting to perform out in the open on the streets.
Emu: Yeah, exactly! I can't wait to do it for real♪ Right, Tsukasa?
Emu: Huh...? Now that I think about it, where is Tsukasa?
Rui: Oh, Emu, did you not see his message?
Rui: Last night, he sent us one saying, “I'll be practicing on my own, so the rest of you head over without me.”
Emu: Oh, gotcha!
Nene: He's been really focused lately.
Rui: Yes, he has. After all, he was given a fairly big role for this production.
Rui: I'm guessing he's having sword fighting practice with Mr. Kijima right now.
Nene: Right... In that case, we should hurry over.
Emu: Okay! Let's go, you guys!!!
Emu: Gooood morni—
Tsukasa: *Roar*
Emu: Wh-What?!?!
Nene: Wh-What's Tsukasa doing...?! Why's he running back and forth like that...?!
Tsukasa: *Roar*
Rui: Could this be a part of his basic training...? Still, he's got a ferocious look on his face.
Emu: That was so cool! Did you hear the way he roared just now?!
Nene: I'm not sure “cool” is the right word. To be honest, he sounded more like a wild animal to me...
Kijima: Ah, good morning to you all!
Kijima: And you're here so early again! I'm impressed!
Emu: Oh, Mr. Kijima, good morning!!!
Nene: So, umm... What's Tsukasa doing? That doesn't look like one of our regular exercises...
Kijima: This? I designed it specifically for Tenma!
Tsukasa: Hm...?!
Tsukasa: Oh, you're all here! I didn't realize... *Cough*
Nene: Whoa! A-Are you okay?!
Tsukasa: I-I'm fine! It's my fault for trying to speak before catching my breath!
Nene: Okay, if you say so...
Tsukasa: Yes, I apologize if I caused you any concern! But I couldn't be better!
Tsukasa: However! I may be done with that exercise, but I don't have time to dawdle.
Tsukasa: I need to have a meal and drink my protein within the next forty-five minutes!
Tsukasa: Let's see... My protein and shaker should be in my bag...
Nene: W-Wow, he...
Emu: He sounds so motivated today!
Rui: Or rather, he's been suddenly awakened. Did something happen?
Tsukasa: Ah, thank you for asking!
Tsukasa: Starting today, I've decided that I'm going to attain a new level of fitness!!!
Nene: A new level of fitness?
Tsukasa: Yes! As you all know, “Ginnosuke's on the Case!” will be showing soon.
Tsukasa: So, yesterday, while working on my sword fighting skills with Mr. Kijima...
Kijima: “Come, Heihachi! Now is our chance to show off our skills!”
Tsukasa: “Yes, Mr. Ginnosuke!”
Mikazukigumi Members: “Alright, get 'em!”
Tsukasa: ...
Tsukasa: (“Ginnosuke's on the Case!” is a fairly standard tale about a detective from the Edo period.)
Tsukasa: (Mr. Kijima plays the protagonist, Ginnosuke, who is the toughest constable in all of ancient Tokyo. No case goes unsolved when his brawn and brains enter the equation.)
Tsukasa: (And I play Heihachi, his detective right-hand man. As such, my sword fighting skills need to be up to snuff.)
Tsukasa: (But Mr. Kijima's sword fighting skills are on another level.)
Tsukasa: (First of all, each move he makes is purposeful and calculated. You can tell that he's used to fighting from his body language.)
Tsukasa: (Not only that, the way he moves meshes seamlessly with Ginnosuke the constable's personality...)
Tsukasa: (Mr. Kijima's even parrying and deflecting attacks in a forceful manner that doesn't match his own personality at all. He must be doing that on purpose.)
Tsukasa: (If I too could mold my body to match that of my character...)
Kijima: Alright, let's take a break here!
Mikazukigumi Members: Okay!
Tsukasa: Excuse me, Mr. Kijima!
Kijima: Hm? How can I help you, Tenma?
Tsukasa: So, I have a question...
Tsukasa: How can I learn to move the way you do?!
Kijima: Huh?
Tsukasa: Ever since we began practicing for “Ginnosuke's on the Case!”, I keep thinking to myself...
Tsukasa: That you wield a sword so elegantly... The way you move your hands and feet... How you're able to truly become your character is just so astonishing...!
Tsukasa: I've been doing my best while training with your troupe, but I still can't move the way I'd like to...
Tsukasa: As an actor, I want to learn to move the way you do, Mr. Kijima!
Tsukasa: So, please teach me! Show me how to emulate what you do...!
Kijima: How...?
Kijima: Well, to put it in simple terms...
Kijima: You need to become more fit!!!!
Tsukasa: Huh...?
Tsukasa: Wait, but... I know that staying fit is important. I was talking about other things that...
Kijima: Stop right there, Tenma!
Kijima: Yes, I understand that “becoming more fit” may sound dull and mundane.
Kijima: But it's very important to you right now. That's what I believe.
Tsukasa: Can you elaborate further...?
Kijima: First, Tenma, your acting skills are already unquestionably good.
Kijima: You've even started thinking about how to improve the way you portray your character by moving more like him. That's very admirable of you...
Tsukasa: Th-Thank you very much...! I feel honored!
Kijima: However, on the other hand...
Kijima: Your body is having trouble keeping up with your mind.
Tsukasa: ...!!!
Kijima: Staged fights and battle involve more than just combat. They're a part of a bigger scene, and each actor needs to move accordingly.
Kijima: In other words, you have to battle while wearing someone else's shoes. Which isn't easy, and requires having fuller control over your body.
Tsukasa: Fuller control...
Kijima: That's right. Based on your current flexibility, as well as the strength of your core and other muscles, your body leaves a lot to be desired...
Kijima: So, in order to achieve a higher level of control, you need to become more fit.
Tsukasa: Y-Yes, I see...! And I completely agree...
Tsukasa: If I don't have the basics down, then I'm never going to solve more complex problems. Does that about sum things up...?
Kijima: Yeah, exactly. There is a chance that you'll succeed based on pure luck, but you wouldn't be able to repeat what you did.
Kijima: Becoming a good actor means having good fundamentals. Work hard on your fitness, and then you'll be able to achieve perfect control over your body.
Tsukasa: Yes, understood!
Tsukasa: ...is what happened!
Tsukasa: Which is why I'm doing everything I can right now to raise my fitness level!
Emu: Now it all makes sense!
Nene: It also explains why you suddenly started drinking protein.
Tsukasa: It's not just protein! Chicken, boiled eggs, broccoli! Everything I need in order to efficiently gain more muscle!
Rui: Hehe. It's like you've turned into an athlete.
Rui: By the way, Mr. Kijima, I have a question regarding what happens after your fundamentals have reached a sufficient level...
Rui: Do you keep on working out in order to put on better portrayals of the characters you play?
Kijima: Yes, of course.
Kijima: Depending on a character's personality, upbringing and such, which muscles I need to tone can change greatly. I do my best to match their situations.
Emu: Whoa...! You work on individual muscles?! That's amazing...!
Nene: Yeah... It's like every fiber of your being is involved in becoming your character.
Kijima: Anyway, to summarize...
Kijima: First, you need to increase your stamina. Once you've done that, you need to think about how you're going to sculpt your body to match your character's.
Kijima: By doing so, you'll slowly come to understand how your character moves and behaves... That's how I've been learning to play my characters until now.
Tsukasa: How my character moves and behaves...
Kijima: That's right. And you feel this incredible rush after you've solved that puzzle! The satisfaction of knowing that your body fully participated in the portrayal of your character!
Kijima: Keep doing your best to solve your character's puzzle, Tenma! I promise to give you all the support I can!
Tsukasa: Thank you! I appreciate it!
Tsukasa: (First, I need to work on my fundamentals...!)
Tsukasa: (Then, I need to learn how to master the way my character moves and behaves! And take my next big step towards stardom!)
Tsukasa: *Roar* Let's do this!!!
